Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of determining deep holes in Reed-Solomon codes, which is a topic in coding theory and information theory (cs.IT). The reduction used in the paper relies on algebraic geometry and the properties of algebraic varieties, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (discrete mathematics) or cs.CG (computational geometry). The paper also mentions the complexity of the problem and the use of estimation techniques, which could place it under cs.CC (computational complexity) or cs.CR (cryptography and security).
